@Annotation - Without changing business logic we give extra functionlaities to our code.
  In spring annotations are places at 
     -> class level.
     -> Field level
     -> method level
     -> constructor level

Spring Core:
-------------
   @Component - Generic anotation for (spring managed bean) creating an object for class in spring container.
       Used when a class dont fit in specific layer.
       utiliy 
       Helpers
       commonn Logics.
   @Service   - this annotation also used for (spring managed bean) creating an object for class in spring container indicates business logic. - 
           Usage - 
           Busines Logic
           calculations
           Processing data

   @Autowired:
      this annotation specifies spring continer to inject dependency into the class. 
   @Configuration 
     We will mention app level configurations in this. EX: what packages has to be scanned for creatin obejcts inside the spring container.

   @Bean: Used in method level, this is used inside configuration class.
   By using this we can make a specific class obejct to get loaded into the container.


